<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Easy pulling in PoP has all but eliminated the need for crowd control, and whats worse, the spell Greater Fetter (which many classes get) actually has a BETTER chance of stopping a monster than the enchanters best mez spell called Bliss. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
2 classes get Greater Fetter.  One of them is Enchanter.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Our ability to contribute DPS to a group has been greatly reduced when compared to how much other classes have been improved on in this area. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Chanters weren't using charm to add dps, in most cases.  They were using it to solo.  Beyond that, nothing has stopped them from using the mob as a group dps enchancer.  It's just made it a lot more dangerous soloing.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Our ability to crowd control is further marginalized by the ineffectiveness of our best mez spell Bliss. It is resisted so often, that many enchanters now use Greater Fetter, and then Bliss to control crowds. Relying solely on Bliss is just asking for trouble. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No chanter I know uses root over mes, except, I imagine, where the situation is especially favorable towards the exchange.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Without charm, or some other meaningful way to contribute to a group, enchanters have been reduced to shamans who cannot slow monsters as well, and cannot backup heal. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Enchanters did not lose charm.  They had the ability changed, a little more dangerous, but still useable.  They're just upset they were spoiled and don't have such a massive dps option with little to no danger to themselves.  Necros were in the same boat, we were spoiled, but no necro I know of felt that it was right to be able to get 3-4 AA in an hour.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>First strike: the affliction focus effects were changed so that only damage causing spells were candidate; this explicitly removed mez and charm from these effects, as well as other such as snare. This increased the mana cost of charming. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
An error is an error.  If they somehow slipped up and CH got added to some effect that reduced mana, and it was left in a while, then taken back out, the clerics would not be stupid enough to whine about this.  They would have realized it was an error and enjoyed it while they could.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Second strike: the two highest level charms for enchanters, Beckon ??? and Command of Druzzil, both had adjustments to magic resistance. These were experimented with on the Test server, and finally removed completely - these had been previous removed from the druid 60+ charm, and were also removed from the mage and necro 60+ charms. The net result was that charm times became far more variable; before, an enchanter with the Total Domination AA level 3 and good gear would expect 80% of charms to run to maximum duration without prior tashing; after, a similar proportion was possible with tashing. Necros have no way of affecting the MR of mobs, so this change alone made charm soloing effectively impossible for necros - although necros had access to other means of soloing. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I can't follow what he's upset about here.  Before you didn't have to use an MR reducing spell only chanters get, and now you do, and this is bad?  Or is this an unneeded cry on the part of necromancers and the other classes?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>all faction changes were removed from non-player race illusions.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>used these various illusions to aid with corpse recoveries, to use werewolf illusion to move around in Velks Lab, for instance.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Not that I have any idea why you'd expect mobs in Velk's Lab to ignore a werewolf in the first place (I would think to most sentient creatures, a werewolf is a bad thing), but I've never known enchanters who were big on being used for CR.<br>
<br>
The post and the examples given by the people in the article sound like nothing but whining by a bunch of children.  Subscribing to this petition and this &quot;protest&quot; only shows your mind is as weak as the people who put this &quot;protest&quot; together.<br>
