Take your power supply out of your computer, (this part is completely painless.....Hmmm well if you have it unplugged when you try it is anyway) and take it down to your local puter shop.   Put it on the counter and tell them you want one just like it, but one that works rather then makes rude noises. Chances are extremely good they will have one for you to take home right then and there, especially if it's one of those super geek puter stores rather then a large commercial chain. then go home and put it back in your puter (a'kay this part can be pain and if you're intimidated by puter guts like I am, this part can take awhile hehe. ) and begin enjoying many consecutive hours of eq entertainment.  (/snicker)<br>
<br>
As far as puter troubles go, this is &quot;good&quot; one to have if you have to have one.  Power supplies are cheap, even power supplies with their own cooling systems are cheap.  They are easy to get parts for, and are relatively simple to install.<br>
